-Fired-up Excited Cookies:
-Base Ingredients
270 g all-purpose flour
150 g granulated sugar
165 g packed brown sugar
16 tbsp butter
1.0 tsp baking soda
1.0 tsp salt
100 g eggs
-Flavor Ingredients
1.0 tbsp black tea
0.5 tsp chamomile
2.0 tsp grapefruit
200 g chocolate
1.0 tsp vanilla
---
Instructions
Step 1: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F.
Step 2: Mix together dry ingredients, combining flour, baking soda, salt, black tea, chamomile, grapefruit in a large bowl. In another bowl, cream together granulated sugar, packed brown sugar and  butter, then add vanilla and eggs.
Step 3: Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients, mixing well. Once mixed, add the chocolate.
Step 4: Let the mixture rest for 7 hours in the refrigerator. On a baking sheet lined with parchment paper, add 55 grams of dough, rolled into a sphere. Bake for 10 minutes, turning the sheet around halfway through the baking time. 
Step 6: Let the cookies cool.